sql:
SELECT name
FROM artists
WHERE artist_id IN (
    SELECT artist_id
    FROM (
        SELECT artist_id, AVG(danceability) AS avg_danceability
        FROM tracks
        GROUP BY artist_id
    ) AS artist_avg_danceability
    WHERE avg_danceability > (
        SELECT AVG(danceability) FROM tracks
    )
);

external_knowledge:
- 'popular tunes' refers to the track titles; 
- 'artists' refers to the names of the musicians; 
- 'musical styles' refers to the genre of the music; 
- 'most loved to the least' is based on the popularity ranking of the tracks (from highest to lowest).

- "musical gardeners" refers to the users who create playlists;
- "gardens" metaphorically describes their collections of tracks (playlists);
- "blossoming tunes" symbolizes tracks with high popularity, where popularity is averaged among the tracks in each user's playlists.

- "Energetic and highly danceable" refers to tracks with high danceability (>0.8) and high energy (>0.8);
- "Subtle volume" means tracks with a loudness less than -5.0;
- "Specific musical mode" refers to tracks with a mode value of 1.

